@10:50 - Opened train #1 raw water valve, and started low lift pump #1 to test after contractors were working on it.  Ran low lift pump #1 at different speeds to test to ensure operation is normal.  While running, the pump interlocked on uncomanded stop, and hydraulic valve uncomanded close.  Worked with Eaton and Lexsan to resolve the issues with Low lift #1 from 11:00 to 11:45.  Ran the low lift #1 to train #1 while tested, caused low tank level alarms in train #1.  Placed low lift #1 back to auto once completed testing, all okay

@11:20 - Backpulse pumps lolo flow and interlock, and train #7 neutralization aborted alarms.  Cause of alarms was the result of the Permeate header draining empty again.  Also caused multiple turbidity faults.  This is a known issue, as the backpulse tanks are drawn down for Maintenance cleans while the plant is off, while also draining the permeate header.  The service water line that normally feeds the backpulse tanks is currently OOS due to a pipe break.  Opened the UV inlet and outlet valves to backfill the permeate line and fill the backpulse tanks.  Worked with Jack P and Jackie Saunders.  Cleared turbidity fault alarms once the common header was full again
@11:55 - Initiated neutralization sequence on train #7 as it had aborted during the previous alarm sequence

